comments: Interesting. I'm guessing you're seeing how people establish patterns of semantics? Like when I saw just school buses, I assumed the word meant "school buses only", and the same with dogs.
what hard to judge exactly which characteristics you were looking - general or specific  (i.e. Buses or Yellow Buses, dogs or just dalmations)
You didn't say it, but I took it that I should remember what I had seen before, e.g. the last one I decided was a sitting dog as opposed to a dalmation
Think I got one of the initial ones wrong, but I enjoyed this experiment.
